The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 February is 38,518 (4,458.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 February, there were 1,378 new confirmed cases (159.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 31 January, there were 2,095 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 34% (717 fewer cases).
